<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef84154b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2542"><num value="2542">§ 2542.</num><heading> Grandfather clause</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall abridge the right of any person, or the successor in interest of the person, to reproduce or sell a variety developed and produced by such person more than one year prior to the effective filing date of an adverse application for a certificate of plant variety protection.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef84154c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/577/tIII/s112">Pub. L. 91–577, title III, § 112</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1555">84 Stat. 1555</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/349/s13/r">Pub. L. 103–349, § 13(r)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-06">Oct. 6, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/3144">108 Stat. 3144</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef84154d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef84154e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef84154f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/349">Pub. L. 103–349</ref> substituted “the successor in interest of the person” for “his successor in interest”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idef841550-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idef841551-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1994 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/103/349">Pub. L. 103–349</ref> effective 180 days after <date date="1994-10-06">Oct. 6, 1994</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/103/349/s15">section 15 of Pub. L. 103–349</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s2401">section 2401 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
